{"author":{"id":"783b610f274a0d93f6239db0fc75d0982606c877a4661d3aea84b42bc3a85cea"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1701799921,"nonce":"9hdgUNevB2tEoSeoc2EtLjEwlGs=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOAW4Y0s5twLle","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/5632#issuecomment-1841346910"},"message":"Hi @bernt-matthias Could you explain what I should do? This isn't for the Bioconductor team, it is for the Galaxy wrapper. Eg trap the problematic usage. \n\nThis tool is very tricky for people to use, and is unique in that the \"order\" of data consumption depends on the order of datasets in the user history, not how they select the inputs on the form, and it must be the same between the two separate input types. BAM input order + BED input order == same or it fails with a scientific warning when the actual problem is mismatched order of the pairing. \n\nWe get a LOT of bug reports for this one, and the solution is complicated. Either copy the datasets in the correct order into a new history OR create collections in the right ordering. In short, forces the user to do somewhat advanced manipulations in Galaxy that are not related to scientific goals. I can't think of any other tool that works this way. I know why it is modeled this way but maybe we can be clever and come up with something better?\n\nI'm not stuck on how this is addressed but improving the usability would be a win.","files":null}]}